    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>
                    Letter from Edward Upward to John F. Lehmann reagrding the book "Journey to the Border"
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            154 Turney Road Dulwich S.E. 21
                        </placeName>
                        <date when="YYYY-MM-DD">
                            1945-12-27
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                             <persName>John F. Lehmann </persName> 
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                             <addrLine> 154 Turney Road Dulwich S.E. 21
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <salute>
                        Dear John, thanks very much for your letter
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    The position at present is that <persName>Mr Tavernier</persName> of <lb/>
                    "<unclear reason="bad writing"> " will, if he wishes to publish a translation <lb/>
                    of <title>Journey to the Border</title>, get in touch with you. In <lb/>
                    that case I should be glad if you would negotiate <lb/>
                    a contract. He hasn't yet seen the book, but the intending<lb/>
                    translation will be discussing it with him, and <persName>Mr Tavernier</persName> <lb/>
                    will have made a decision by the time he comes over here <lb/>
                    in the new year <lb/>
                    I am still working at the new novel. I think <lb/>
                    that something worth while will come of it in the end
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        Yours ever, Edward
                    </salute>
                    <signed/>
                    <seg>
                        <gap/>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
